column1: 55,"WN272","Software","  The source code of [MAPS.ME](http://maps.me/de/home) [has been published under Apache License at Github](https://github.com/mapsme/omim). The Russian OSM blog [reports about it](http://shtosm.ru/all/otkrytie-goda/). MAPS.ME is an offline map application based on Qt5 framwork for Android, iOS, Windows, Mac and Linux. Teams of Wochennotiz and weeklyOSM are looking for someone who wants to blog at our blog about a hands-on of MAPS.ME and comparison with other OSM-bases offline map applications. Some users at the OsmAnd Google Group [think](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/osmand/7MAbPRjoNmk) that the rendering engine of MAPS.ME is superior to the OsmAnd rendering engine.",9

column1: 2771,"WN320","About us","We were [asked](http://blog.openstreetmap.de/blog/2016/09/wochennotiz-nr-319/#comment-225306) ![(Deutsch)](http://blog.openstreetmap.de/wp-uploads//2016/05/de.svg) after publishing issue 319 why MAPS.ME was marked as non-free software. MAPS.ME is not free software because it [contains](https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://github.com/mapsme/omim/blob/master/data/copyright.html) [Code2000](http://de.fonts2u.com/code2000.schriftart) font which is a shareware. We mark a software as free software if all its parts are free software as defined by [Debian Free Software Guidelines](https://www.debian.org/social_contract#guidelines).",9

5860,"WN383","Other Geo Things","Maps.me is the cycling app of the week at [road.cc](http://road.cc/content/tech-news/232323-cycling-app-week-mapsme).",9

5993,"WN386","Other Geo Things","Using Waze or Google Maps is [highly problematic](https://www.wired.com/story/palestine-jerusalem-mapping) in the Gaza strip. Whether the use of a road is advisable or even allowed depends on whether one is Palestinian, Israeli or a resident of specific zones. Local Palestinians had to start creating their own maps, mostly helped by using Maps.me.",9

6086,"WN389","Community","Joost Schouppe has [created](http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/joost%20schouppe/diary/43057) an analysis of the OSM Notes. Among other things, he discusses the effects of Maps.me.",9

7760,"WN425","Mapping","Osmose [now allows](https://twitter.com/osmose_qa/status/1038469872483745792?s=19) potential errors to be exported as KML files. You can import these files into apps, such as Maps.me, to assist in checking on the ground.",9

8063,"WN432","Software","We have reported [before](http://www.weeklyosm.eu/archives/10507) rescues of hikers occasioned by the use of OSM without evaluating the terrain by other means, such as topo maps. Now, according to [CBC Canada](https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/michael-buckingham-vancouver-hiker-rescued-north-shore-crown-mountain-1.4857646), a hiker had to be rescued by helicopter from the top of a cliff in British Columbia. Allegedly the hiker was benighted because they relied on Maps.me for an estimate of how long it would take to walk in the mountainous terrain. An issue was [reported](https://github.com/mapsme/omitm/issues/6980) in 2017, but it is not entirely clear if the situation still exists with the current version.",9

9576,"WN463","Mapping","Developers of the Maps.me navigator, which uses OSM data, [created](https://lists.openstreetmap.org/pipermail/talk-transit/2019-May/002171.html) a [validator](http://osm-subway.maps.me/) for underground railways (subways/metros) all over the world.",9

9808,"WN468","Software","The developers of Maps.Me have significantly [simplified](https://github.com/mapsme/dockerfiles/tree/master/maps_generator) the process of installing a map generator for their application. It's now available as a docker-container which allows the creation of fresh maps for Maps.Me even for inexperienced users. It currently only works on Linux.",9

11147,"WN498","Community","User Vascom has [started](https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?id=68433)  ![(ru)](https://blog.openstreetmap.de/wp-uploads/2016/12/ru.svg)    (automatic [translation](https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=auto&tl=EN&u=https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?id=68433)) to assemble weekly maps for Maps.Me. So far, he has [covered](https://hide.webhop.me/mapsme/) all regions of Russia, Ukraine and Belarus.",9

11419,"WN503","Programming","Russian user Vascom, who recently began to create weekly [maps](https://hide.webhop.me/mapsme/) for the Maps.Me app for all regions of Russia and CIS countries, [shared](https://github.com/Vascom/mapsme) the scripts he uses to do this.",9

11765,"WN511","Software","As we have noted [before](http://weeklyosm.eu/archives/12843/#wn498_21838), OSM user Vascom has started assembling [new maps](https://hide.webhop.me/mapsme/) for Maps.Me. Not so long ago he [added](https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?pid=783743#p783743) ![(ru)](https://blog.openstreetmap.de/wp-uploads/2016/12/ru.svg) (automatic [translation](https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=auto&tl=EN&u=https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?pid=783743#p783743)) new countries: Czech Republic and Poland.",9

11931,"WN515","Community","As we reported earlier ([#498](http://weeklyosm.eu/archives/12843/#wn498_21838)), OSM user Vascom has started to assemble [maps](https://hide.webhop.me/mapsme/) from Maps.Me on a weekly basis. Not so long ago, he [added](https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?pid=786827#p786827) ![(ru)](https://blog.openstreetmap.de/wp-uploads/2016/12/ru.svg) (automatic [translation](https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=auto&tl=EN&u=https://forum.openstreetmap.org/viewtopic.php?pid=786827#p786827)) 6 new countries: Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Hungary, Romania, Bosnia and Herzegovina. In addition, he started making daily [builds](https://hide.webhop.me/mapsme/daily/). However, these are for only two locations: Moscow and the West of the Moscow region.",9

13291,"WN544","Software","Maps.Me version 2.0 elicited some hostile feedback on [twitter](https://twitter.com/MAPS_ME/status/1340339215918391298). The [related discussion](https://www.reddit.com/r/openstreetmap/comments/khsjqx/mapsme_seems_have_reached_its_end/) on the OSM subreddit is more informative. There seems to be a general loss of both features and functionality, in the version for Apple devices only, at present.",9

13431,"WN547","Software","The Maps.me GitHub repositories have now been [cloned](https://github.com/omapsapp), and a [preliminary website](https://omaps.app/) is available for the Maps.me fork OMaps, which has arisen in response to the problems with Maps.me [we reported earlier](https://weeklyosm.eu/archives/14122#wn545_24052).",9

13513,"WN549","Maps","Christopher Beddow [writes](https://bedogged.substack.com/p/the-mobile-map-app-part-ii-pivoting), in his second of three blog posts, about the background and importance of Maps.me.",9

18749,"WN698","Software","A recent change to Organic Maps, which [added](https://github.com/organicmaps/organicmaps/pull/6523) a commercial hotel review platform as a partner link in the hope of opening up a new revenue stream, had led to heated debate about whether this was advertising or not (we [reported](https://weeklyosm.eu/archives/16873#wn697_29523) earlier). Some users had [expressed](https://gitlab.com/fdroid/fdroiddata/-/merge_requests/14082) the fear that the developers were turning Organic Maps into Maps.me 2.0, from which this app originally split off from for precisely these reasons. In addition, the main developers' handling of the community's objections was criticised, with some then apologising for this.",9

19820,"WN722","OSM in the media","_MSPoweruser_ [compared](https://mspoweruser.com/maps-me-vs-google-maps/) Maps.me and Google Maps, rating their strengths and weaknesses in several categories, including offline capabilities, user interface, search functionality, accuracy, and additional features, to help users decide which mapping application best suits their navigation and exploration needs.",9
